      "description": "Originating in the central parts of the Eurasian Steppe, the Sarmatians were part of the wider Scythian cultures (Probably of Iranian or Turkish origin.), which moved increasing west over time. By the time that the Western Roman Empire was in decline, the Sarmatians were assimilating into the invading Vandals or Goths, being absorbed by Early Slavs, or becoming the Alans of the Northern Caucasus.",
      "restricted": "true"
    },
